Title: NAVIGATION / MULTI INFO DISPLAY: NAVIGATION RECEIVER: REMOVAL; 2019 MY Prius [12/2018 - 08/2019]

REMOVAL

CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

The necessary procedures (adjustment, calibration, initialization, or registration) that must be performed after parts are removed and installed, or replaced during navigation receiver assembly removal/installation are shown below.

Necessary Procedures After Parts Removed/Installed/Replaced

Necessary Procedure

Effect/Inoperative Function when Necessary Procedure not Performed

PROCEDURE

1. PRECAUTION

NOTICE:

After turning the power switch off, waiting time may be required before disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal. Therefore, make sure to read the disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal notices before proceeding with work.

2. DISCONNECT CABLE FROM NEGATIVE AUXILIARY BATTERY TERMINAL

Click here

3. REMOVE INSTRUMENT PANEL FINISH PANEL END RH

Click here

4. REMOVE CENTER INSTRUMENT CLUSTER FINISH PANEL SUB-ASSEMBLY (for 7 Inch Display)

Click here

5. REMOVE NAVIGATION RECEIVER ASSEMBLY WITH BRACKET (for 7 Inch Display)

(a) Remove the 4 bolts.

(b) Pull the navigation receiver assembly with bracket toward the rear of the vehicle and disengage the 2 guides.

Remove in this Direction

(c) Disconnect each connector and remove the navigation receiver assembly with bracket.

6. REMOVE CENTER INSTRUMENT CLUSTER FINISH PANEL UPPER (for 11.6 Inch Display)

Click here

7. REMOVE CENTER INSTRUMENT CLUSTER FINISH PANEL SUB-ASSEMBLY WITH NAVIGATION RECEIVER ASSEMBLY (for 11.6 Inch Display)

Click here

8. REMOVE INSTRUMENT CLUSTER FINISH PANEL SUB-ASSEMBLY (for 11.6 Inch Display)

(a) Disconnect the connector.

(b) Remove the 3 screws.

(c) Disengage the 7 guides to remove the instrument cluster finish panel sub-assembly as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

9. REMOVE CENTER INSTRUMENT CLUSTER FINISH PANEL SUB-ASSEMBLY (for 11.6 Inch Display)

(a) Remove the 3 screws.

(b) Disengage the 7 guides to remove the center instrument cluster finish panel sub-assembly as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

10. DISCONNECT STEREO COMPONENT TUNER ASSEMBLY WITH WIRE (w/ Satellite Radio)

(a) for 7 Inch Display:

(1) Disconnect the 3 connectors to disconnect the stereo component tuner assembly with wire.

(b) for 11.6 Inch Display:

(1) Disengage the clamp.

(2) Disconnect the 3 connectors to disconnect the stereo component tuner assembly with wire.

11. REMOVE HAZARD WARNING SIGNAL SWITCH ASSEMBLY (for 11.6 Inch Display)

(a) Disengage the 2 claws to remove the hazard warning signal switch assembly.

12. REMOVE NO. 1 RADIO BRACKET (for 7 Inch Display)

(a) w/o Satellite Radio:

(1) Remove the 3 screws and No. 1 radio bracket.

(b) w/ Satellite Radio:

(1) Remove the 5 screws and No. 1 radio bracket.

13. REMOVE NO. 1 RADIO BRACKET (for 11.6 Inch Display)

(a) w/o Satellite Radio:

(1) Remove the 3 screws and No. 1 radio bracket.

(b) w/ Satellite Radio:

(1) Remove the 5 screws and No. 1 radio bracket.

14. REMOVE NO. 2 RADIO BRACKET (for 7 Inch Display)

(a) w/o Satellite Radio:

(1) Remove the 3 screws and No. 2 radio bracket.

(b) w/ Satellite Radio:

(1) Remove the 5 screws and No. 2 radio bracket.

15. REMOVE NO. 2 RADIO BRACKET (for 11.6 Inch Display)

(a) w/o Satellite Radio:

(1) Remove the 3 screws and No. 2 radio bracket.

(b) w/ Satellite Radio:

(1) Remove the 5 screws and No. 2 radio bracket.

16. REMOVE STEREO COMPONENT TUNER ASSEMBLY WITH WIRE (w/ Satellite Radio)

17. REMOVE NAVIGATION RECEIVER ASSEMBLY
